    },
    "Background": {
      "text": "Prolonged fever of unknown origin without identified cause generally has favorable prognosis.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Original definition\n[1]\nFever >38.3 C on several occasions\nLasting for at least 3 weeks\nNo clear diagnosis after 1 week inpatient workup\nNewer definition\n[2]\n- \"Prolonged fever\" with:\n3 outpatient visits without identifying a cause\nor\n3 inpatient days without identifying a cause\nor\n1 week of “intelligent and invasive” ambulatory investigation",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
